[Our thanks to Patricia Burke and James Alexander for their useful and instructive comments.

I would point out that the UK had for decades a 6 months quarantine policy for all dogs and cats entering the country and this was frequently utilized. We brought 2 cats from the US in 1965 and we were met at Tilbury docks by a veterinary officer who collected the cats and had them transported to a certified facility in the Midlands. When we visited them there were some 20+ other cats also under quarantine. Now they have to have been vaccinated and are demonstrating an antibody titer. - Mod.MHJ]
